Loan Data from Prosper¶

by: Mohamed Abd Al-mgyd.¶

Preliminary Wrangling¶

Dataset "https://www.google.com/url?q=https://s3.amazonaws.com/udacity-hosted-downloads/ud651/prosperLoanData.csv&sa=D&ust=1554484977406000".

This data set contains 113,937 loans with 81 variables on each loan, including loan amount, borrower rate (or interest rate), current loan status, borrower income, and many others.

What is the structure of your dataset?¶

This data set contains 105421 loans with 11 variables on each loan ,(MemberKey , Term . . . Recommendations).

What is/are the main feature(s) of interest in your dataset?¶

I am interested in calculating : A- Knowing the variables that affect acceptance or rejection of the loan request. B- Knowing the variables that affect the interest rate (borrower APR). C- Are there differences between loan sizes?

By studying some of the borrower-related variables (such as the employment status) and associated with a loan (such as Loan Original Amount).

What features in the dataset do you think will help support your investigation into your feature(s) of interest?¶

Anticipation : A. Believe that (amount of the total loan , employment status and employment status duration ) have a negative impact on the annual interest rate of the loan. B - I also believe that (loan duration and The number of overdue installments) have a positive impact on the annual interest rate of the loan.
